---
title: Hoisin-Marinated Rib-Eye Steak with Bok Choy, Scallion Pesto, and Mashed Potatoes
description: Steak may be classic bistro fare, but that doesn’t mean that it can’t look beyond tradition. In fact, this version is proudly border-hopping. The meat is marinated hoisin and soy sauces, which lend Asian-style flavors and incredible depth. Then, a scallion pesto, punctuated by ginger and garlic, is drizzled on top. The mashed potatoes on the side are classic and buttery, as potatoes should be. But to keep things lively, they’re accompanied by crisp, stir-fried bok choy stalks.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hoisin-marinated-rib-eye-steak-ce4f1521.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hoisin-marinated-rib-eye-steak-5a53acb4c2880001c03e5cf2-7ad1b886.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-marinated-rib-eye-steak-5a53acb4c2880001c03e5cf2
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 1180 kcal
  fat: 89 g
  saturated fat: 30 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 15 g
